- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on malware propagation and its impact on system security.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of a malware analysis framework to analyse the samples.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper may use machine learning techniques to analyse the malware samples.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as malware propagation often involves exploiting vulnerabilities in networked systems.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a less likely category, but still possible as malware propagation can also occur through distributed systems.
